        "materials_required": [
            "Rino software",
            "Installation foam",
            "Gorilla glue",
            "Plywood",
            "Plaster",
            "Mould soap",
            "Cottle boards",
            "Casting slip",
            "Clay",
            "Glaze",
            "Ceramic decals",
            "Cone pack (Cone 017, Cone 018)",
            "RED Mudtool rib"
        ],
        "description": "This project outlines the process of creating ceramic forms using computer-generated models in Rhino, CNC milling, mould making, slipcasting/press moulding, firing, and applying ceramic decals.",
        "steps": [
            "Create ceramic forms in Rino using profile lines, revolve commands, polygons, and lofting. Cap the forms and construct planes with keys for milling.",
            "CNC mill the forms from installation foam, using roughing and finishing stages. Glue foam layers to plywood for milling.",
            "Make plaster moulds by preparing mixing materials, building walls around the object, sealing with clay, applying mould soap and Vaseline, calculating plaster amount, mixing/pouring plaster, and allowing the mould to dry.",
            "Slipcast or press mould using the dried moulds. For slip casting, secure the mould, pour slip, and let it sit. For press moulding, press clay into the mould and smooth the surface.",
            "Fire the ceramic objects in at least two firings: bisque firing to cone 01 and glaze firing to cone 6. Adjust temperatures based on clay and glaze.",
            "Apply ceramic decals by deciding the placement, cutting out the decal, removing the paper backing in water, placing it on the ceramic surface, and squeegeeing excess water.",
            "Fire the decals in a manual kiln. Place objects in the middle with a cone pack, prop open the lid, turn knobs to low, medium, and high, wait for color, remove the brick, and turn off knobs when the first cone drops."
        ]
    }
